Have the following code in an extension, which will set decorations on visible editors every 100ms.

```typescript
setInterval(() => {
    const decoration = vscode.window.createTextEditorDecorationType({});
    vscode.window.visibleTextEditors.forEach(e => {
        e.setDecorations(decoration, []);
    })
}, 100);
```

If you click around the explorer and open up different files, you'll see `setDecorations on invisible editor` warnings in the dev tools. There's no apparent way I could avoid them.

---

A bit worse:

```typescript
setInterval(() => {
    const decoration = vscode.window.createTextEditorDecorationType({});
    vscode.window.visibleTextEditors.forEach(e => {
        e.document;
    })
}, 100);
```

